description: English theory +‎ -etic, from Latin theōrēticus, from Ancient Greek θεωρητικός (theōrētikós).

adjectives.description: theoretic (comparative more theoretic, superlative most theoretic)

entries.meaning: Concerned with theories or hypotheses rather than with practical matters.
examples: We shall, therefore, only very humbly submit whether the whole statement be not rather too theoretic and somewhat too darkly adumbrated in ambiguous phraseology for plain, uncollegian understandings.

entries.meaning: Existing only in theory, not proven in reality.
